WEBVTT

00:00:09.687 --> 00:00:11.690
[coughing]

00:00:14.529 --> 00:00:16.533
[panting]

00:00:17.803 --> 00:00:18.771
[winces]

00:00:18.804 --> 00:00:20.775
<i>[ominous music]</i>

00:00:20.808 --> 00:00:22.779
[shuddering]

00:00:22.812 --> 00:00:25.317
<i>The numbness is so severe.</i>

00:00:26.920 --> 00:00:28.524
<i>These needles.</i>

00:00:28.558 --> 00:00:31.897
<i>I may have been able
to escape the water pot...</i>

00:00:31.931 --> 00:00:33.534
<i>but my strength...</i>

00:00:34.502 --> 00:00:37.207
[metal clatters]

00:00:38.009 --> 00:00:41.583
<i>K--Kotetsu, are you...</i>

00:00:42.652 --> 00:00:44.421
- [murmuring]

00:00:46.793 --> 00:00:48.329
[metal clangs]

00:00:49.398 --> 00:00:50.167
[gasps]

00:00:50.200 --> 00:00:53.575
<i>My strength... is sapped.</i>

00:00:53.608 --> 00:00:55.111
- [wailing]

00:00:55.144 --> 00:00:57.114
<i>- There's nothing...</i>

00:00:57.148 --> 00:00:58.585
<i>I can...</i>

00:00:58.618 --> 00:01:02.291
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:01:02.324 --> 00:01:04.495
- I know you can do it,
Muichiro.

00:01:04.529 --> 00:01:06.566
Now, stand up!

00:01:07.535 --> 00:01:08.771
<i>- Father.</i>

00:01:09.806 --> 00:01:11.811
<i>["Kizuna no Kiseki" playing]</i>

00:01:11.844 --> 00:01:18.857
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:02:41.891 --> 00:02:43.894
<i>[singers vocalizing]</i>

00:02:49.072 --> 00:02:50.407
- [groans]

00:02:51.208 --> 00:02:52.879
<i>That's right.</i>

00:02:52.912 --> 00:02:55.216
<i>My father was a lumberman.</i>

00:02:56.018 --> 00:02:58.189
<i>And as his son,</i>

00:02:58.223 --> 00:03:01.495
<i>I would help him cut down trees
whenever I could.</i>

00:03:08.076 --> 00:03:09.946
- [sighs]

00:03:09.979 --> 00:03:10.981
<i>- I remember.</i>

00:03:12.619 --> 00:03:13.588
- Eh?

00:03:13.621 --> 00:03:14.522
[laughs]

00:03:15.691 --> 00:03:20.802
<i>I remember that I used
to love helping Father work.</i>

00:03:20.835 --> 00:03:23.073
[strong winds blowing]

00:03:23.106 --> 00:03:26.179
[woman coughing]

00:03:26.212 --> 00:03:28.349
- Hang in there, mother!

00:03:28.382 --> 00:03:31.122
Father just went out
to get you some herbs, so...

00:03:31.155 --> 00:03:32.793
Mother!

00:03:32.826 --> 00:03:35.598
- [gasping]

00:03:35.631 --> 00:03:36.967
[water splashes]

00:03:38.069 --> 00:03:39.606
<i>- She's burning up.</i>

00:03:52.866 --> 00:03:54.569
Here. Take my blanket.

00:03:54.602 --> 00:03:56.472
That should help. Right, Mother?

00:03:58.644 --> 00:04:00.047
- So cold...

00:04:00.080 --> 00:04:01.182
- [gasps]

00:04:01.215 --> 00:04:02.986
[sighs]

00:04:03.019 --> 00:04:04.321
Hang on!

00:04:04.355 --> 00:04:06.994
Father will be back soon,
all right?

00:04:07.027 --> 00:04:09.098
<i>[soft music]</i>

00:04:09.131 --> 00:04:11.335
[thunder crashing]

00:04:12.639 --> 00:04:14.642
- [panting]

00:04:19.953 --> 00:04:21.021
Ah.

00:04:24.797 --> 00:04:27.067
[grunting]

00:04:29.472 --> 00:04:30.875
- [ground crumbles]
- [gasps]

00:04:35.985 --> 00:04:40.426
<i>- That day, I lost two people
who were dear to me.</i>

00:04:41.797 --> 00:04:44.702
<i>Both my mother and my father
passed away.</i>

00:04:46.674 --> 00:04:50.013
<i>I was ten years old,
without any parents.</i>

00:04:51.249 --> 00:04:53.987
<i>I was ten years old
and completely alone.</i>

00:04:57.060 --> 00:04:58.063
- Muichiro?

00:04:58.096 --> 00:04:59.065
- Huh?

00:04:59.098 --> 00:05:01.671
<i>No, that's not right.</i>

00:05:01.704 --> 00:05:04.642
<i>I was 11 when I
found myself alone.</i>

00:05:05.812 --> 00:05:09.686
<i>Before then, I used
to have a twin brother...</i>

00:05:11.289 --> 00:05:12.391
<i>an older brother,</i>

00:05:12.424 --> 00:05:14.394
<i>and his name was Yuichiro.</i>

00:05:15.196 --> 00:05:17.467
[birds trilling]

00:05:18.804 --> 00:05:21.142
- Kindness does no good
for anyone.

00:05:21.175 --> 00:05:25.350
If you try to help somebody
in need, you'll only get hurt.

00:05:25.383 --> 00:05:27.454
- That's not true.

00:05:27.487 --> 00:05:29.258
Whatever you do
to help others

00:05:29.291 --> 00:05:33.166
has a way of coming back around
and helping yourself someday.

00:05:33.199 --> 00:05:34.803
That's what Father said.

00:05:34.836 --> 00:05:37.040
- You're regurgitating
the words of a man

00:05:37.074 --> 00:05:40.414
who got himself killed
trying to help someone else.

00:05:41.216 --> 00:05:43.419
- How could you
say something so cold?

00:05:43.453 --> 00:05:45.591
He died trying
to save our mother!

00:05:45.624 --> 00:05:47.628
- As if a few herbs
would have done anything

00:05:47.662 --> 00:05:49.566
to heal her at that point.

00:05:49.600 --> 00:05:51.202
Don't be so stupid.

00:05:51.235 --> 00:05:53.439
- Don't say such awful things!

00:05:53.472 --> 00:05:56.011
- If he hadn't gone out
in the middle of a storm,

00:05:56.045 --> 00:05:58.818
maybe we would have only
lost our mother that night.

00:05:58.851 --> 00:06:01.222
- Please stop
saying things like that!

00:06:01.255 --> 00:06:02.457
That's going too far!

00:06:02.490 --> 00:06:05.064
- I'm only telling you
how it is.

00:06:05.097 --> 00:06:07.101
And stop being so noisy.

00:06:07.134 --> 00:06:08.737
You might attract boars.

00:06:09.639 --> 00:06:11.308
I guess the "mu" in Muichiro

00:06:11.342 --> 00:06:13.413
stands for "incompetence."

00:06:13.446 --> 00:06:15.484
This conversation
is meaningless.

00:06:15.518 --> 00:06:18.089
After all,
you can't change the past.

00:06:19.191 --> 00:06:20.528
Or maybe the "mu" in Muichiro

00:06:20.561 --> 00:06:22.163
stands for "meaningless."

00:06:23.967 --> 00:06:25.638
- [gasps]

00:06:29.712 --> 00:06:32.551
<i>He was unsympathetic
and spoke harshly.</i>

00:06:33.353 --> 00:06:35.725
<i>I feel that, in a way,</i>

00:06:35.758 --> 00:06:38.530
<i>I acted like him
after I had amnesia.</i>

00:06:40.935 --> 00:06:43.373
<i>Life with my brother
wasn't easy.</i>

00:06:43.406 --> 00:06:45.644
<i>If anything, it was stifling.</i>

00:06:46.445 --> 00:06:48.483
<i>I was sure he despised me,</i>

00:06:48.517 --> 00:06:49.986
<i>and because of that,</i>

00:06:50.019 --> 00:06:53.426
<i>I couldn't help but think
of him as a cold person.</i>

00:06:54.529 --> 00:06:56.967
<i>I remember
the seasons changed...</i>

00:06:58.069 --> 00:06:59.906
<i>and it was spring.</i>

00:06:59.939 --> 00:07:02.144
[birds chirping]

00:07:02.177 --> 00:07:03.346
I'll be back.

00:07:03.379 --> 00:07:04.716
I'm gonna fetch some water.

00:07:04.750 --> 00:07:07.555
- You still haven't gotten any?

00:07:08.456 --> 00:07:09.659
- [sighs]

00:07:23.185 --> 00:07:24.221
[gasps]

00:07:24.254 --> 00:07:27.460
<i>[soft music]</i>

00:07:31.169 --> 00:07:33.774
<i>The first time I saw her,
I couldn't believe it.</i>

00:07:34.576 --> 00:07:36.613
<i>She was so beautiful...</i>

00:07:36.646 --> 00:07:38.917
<i>I thought she was
a white-birch spirit.</i>

00:07:39.919 --> 00:07:41.590
<i>[wind blowing]</i>

00:07:41.623 --> 00:07:42.925
<i>[sword slices]</i>

00:07:45.931 --> 00:07:47.602
<i>[wind blowing]</i>

00:07:47.635 --> 00:07:49.104
<i>[sword slices]</i>

00:07:51.409 --> 00:07:52.478
<i>[Muichiro] It turns out</i>

00:07:52.512 --> 00:07:54.482
<i>this person
was the master's wife,</i>

00:07:54.516 --> 00:07:56.185
<i>who came to visit us,</i>

00:07:56.219 --> 00:07:59.793
<i>which meant she traveled
all the way up the mountain.</i>

00:07:59.826 --> 00:08:01.128
<i>But...</i>

00:08:02.130 --> 00:08:03.099
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:08:03.132 --> 00:08:04.201
[door slams]

00:08:04.234 --> 00:08:05.638
<i>- ...in the end,</i>

00:08:05.671 --> 00:08:07.842
<i>my brother just spewed
his usual insults</i>

00:08:07.875 --> 00:08:10.079
<i>and drove Lady Amane away.</i>

00:08:11.550 --> 00:08:12.885
- Can you believe it?
- [chopping]

00:08:12.919 --> 00:08:15.023
She says our ancestors
were swordsmen!

00:08:15.056 --> 00:08:18.463
Apparently we're descendants
of an amazing swordsman

00:08:18.496 --> 00:08:20.333
who used something
called First Breathing!

00:08:20.367 --> 00:08:22.204
- Why should I care?

00:08:22.237 --> 00:08:23.574
Wash the rice already.

00:08:23.607 --> 00:08:25.711
- Hey, let's become swordsmen!

00:08:25.744 --> 00:08:27.749
It's hard to believe
demons exist

00:08:27.782 --> 00:08:29.418
and are out there
hurting people.

00:08:29.451 --> 00:08:31.890
If we can do something to help,
we should!

00:08:31.923 --> 00:08:34.027
Right? So let's
become swordsmen

00:08:34.061 --> 00:08:36.132
and save the people
who are suffering!

00:08:36.165 --> 00:08:37.535
If we do it together--

00:08:49.926 --> 00:08:51.763
Uh...

00:08:51.796 --> 00:08:54.468
- What makes you think
you could ever save anybody?!

00:08:54.502 --> 00:08:56.138
You can't cook rice on your own,

00:08:56.171 --> 00:08:59.411
and you're gonna be a swordsman
and save others?!

00:08:59.445 --> 00:09:01.650
Give me a break, Muichiro!

00:09:01.683 --> 00:09:03.520
You sound
like Mother and Father,

00:09:03.554 --> 00:09:05.223
spouting that kind of nonsense!

00:09:05.256 --> 00:09:07.294
Stop being so optimistic!

00:09:07.327 --> 00:09:08.697
Your mind is poisoned!

00:09:08.731 --> 00:09:11.068
Just like Mother,
who told us she was fine

00:09:11.101 --> 00:09:12.738
and then worked
until she collapsed!

00:09:12.771 --> 00:09:15.878
Like Father, who got killed
trying to find some herbs!

00:09:15.912 --> 00:09:19.953
Even after I tried to stop him!

00:09:19.986 --> 00:09:23.593
Even after I begged Mother
to rest over and over!

00:09:23.627 --> 00:09:26.398
The only kind of people
who can help others

00:09:26.432 --> 00:09:28.571
are people
who were chosen to do so!

00:09:28.604 --> 00:09:31.342
Our ancestors
may have been swordsmen,

00:09:31.375 --> 00:09:33.380
but we are
just two hopeless orphans!

00:09:33.413 --> 00:09:36.218
People like us are useless!

00:09:36.251 --> 00:09:37.889
We're only good for one thing,

00:09:37.922 --> 00:09:40.695
and that's dying in the street
like dogs!

00:09:40.728 --> 00:09:43.099
Our parents met the same fate
to prove it!

00:09:43.133 --> 00:09:45.871
We'll only end up
getting used by that woman!

00:09:45.904 --> 00:09:47.808
Why do you think
she came all the way here?!

00:09:47.842 --> 00:09:50.848
We're never talking
about this again. Got it?

00:09:50.881 --> 00:09:52.952
Now hurry up,
and get dinner ready!

00:09:55.624 --> 00:09:57.661
- [cries]

00:09:59.264 --> 00:10:03.038
<i>After that incident, we stopped
speaking to each other.</i>

00:10:05.711 --> 00:10:07.782
<i>Except for the one time
we fought briefly</i>

00:10:07.815 --> 00:10:10.654
<i>when my brother
hurled water at Lady Amane,</i>

00:10:10.688 --> 00:10:13.527
<i>who'd traveled up the mountain
to visit us again.</i>

00:10:13.560 --> 00:10:15.764
[panting]

00:10:18.670 --> 00:10:19.906
[yelps]

00:10:21.643 --> 00:10:23.847
[panting]

00:10:45.457 --> 00:10:46.693
[cicadas buzzing]

00:10:46.727 --> 00:10:48.630
<i>Then summer came.</i>

00:10:48.664 --> 00:10:50.701
<i>It was blisteringly hot,</i>

00:10:50.735 --> 00:10:53.272
<i>so my brother and I
were always irritable.</i>

00:10:54.341 --> 00:10:55.845
<i>It was a hot night.</i>

00:10:55.878 --> 00:10:57.515
<i>The cicadas were singing.</i>

00:10:57.548 --> 00:10:59.752
[soft buzzing]

00:11:04.128 --> 00:11:05.429
[groans]

00:11:08.068 --> 00:11:09.170
[sighs]

00:11:15.684 --> 00:11:16.886
[sighs]

00:11:21.195 --> 00:11:22.196
[sighs]

00:11:26.639 --> 00:11:27.875
[sighs]

00:11:29.145 --> 00:11:30.146
Hmm?

00:11:35.991 --> 00:11:36.859
- [sighs]

00:11:36.893 --> 00:11:38.897
[cicadas buzzing]

00:11:40.601 --> 00:11:42.237
[buzzing stops]

00:11:42.270 --> 00:11:43.272
- [gasps]

00:11:43.305 --> 00:11:44.374
<i>[tense music]</i>

00:11:44.407 --> 00:11:45.778
- Ah, damn it.

00:11:45.811 --> 00:11:48.517
Nothing but
a couple of brats, huh?

00:11:48.550 --> 00:11:50.688
Tch! Whatever.

00:11:50.721 --> 00:11:51.823
- Muichiro!

00:11:51.856 --> 00:11:54.294
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:11:56.298 --> 00:11:58.704
[screams]

00:11:58.737 --> 00:12:01.676
- Brother! Brother!
- [moaning]

00:12:01.710 --> 00:12:03.980
- [laughs]

00:12:04.849 --> 00:12:07.053
- [wailing]
- [grunting]

00:12:09.626 --> 00:12:11.863
- Shut up! Shut up!

00:12:12.665 --> 00:12:13.834
You're too noisy.

00:12:13.867 --> 00:12:16.506
You can cry for help,
but no one's coming

00:12:16.539 --> 00:12:19.913
to help a couple of useless
lumbermen like yourselves.

00:12:19.946 --> 00:12:23.052
Since it doesn't matter
whether you exist or not.

00:12:23.086 --> 00:12:26.359
After all,
your lives are worthless!

00:12:26.392 --> 00:12:28.262
- [whimpers]

00:12:28.295 --> 00:12:29.966
[squelch]

00:12:29.999 --> 00:12:33.740
<i>- At that moment,
all I could see was red.</i>

00:12:33.773 --> 00:12:37.982
<i>I went into a violent
and uncontrollable rage,</i>

00:12:38.015 --> 00:12:41.021
<i>one that boiled
from the pit of my stomach.</i>

00:12:41.055 --> 00:12:43.126
<i>It came to me naturally.</i>

00:12:43.159 --> 00:12:47.635
<i>And while I can't remember
exactly what happened next,</i>

00:12:47.669 --> 00:12:49.438
<i>I still hear that roar.</i>

00:12:49.471 --> 00:12:50.407
<i>Even now...</i>

00:12:50.440 --> 00:12:51.341
[screaming]

00:12:51.375 --> 00:12:53.012
<i>...I can't believe
a sound like that</i>

00:12:53.045 --> 00:12:54.515
<i>came from my throat,</i>

00:12:54.549 --> 00:12:55.884
<i>from my own mouth.</i>

00:13:03.767 --> 00:13:04.836
[sighs]

00:13:04.870 --> 00:13:07.107
<i>Before I knew it,</i>

00:13:07.140 --> 00:13:09.344
<i>the demon was
on the brink of death.</i>

00:13:09.378 --> 00:13:12.952
<i>But apparently it couldn't die,
even with its head smashed in,</i>

00:13:12.985 --> 00:13:14.689
<i>so it was suffering.</i>

00:13:14.722 --> 00:13:16.926
[demon gurgling]

00:13:21.101 --> 00:13:24.107
[gags]

00:13:26.178 --> 00:13:28.249
<i>- Soon after,
the sun began to rise,</i>

00:13:28.283 --> 00:13:31.388
<i>and the demon turned to dust
and vanished.</i>

00:13:32.357 --> 00:13:34.494
<i>But I couldn't care less
about that.</i>

00:13:36.232 --> 00:13:38.369
[groaning]

00:13:39.939 --> 00:13:42.043
<i>All I wanted
was to get to Yuichiro</i>

00:13:42.077 --> 00:13:44.447
<i>and tend to his wounds,</i>

00:13:44.481 --> 00:13:47.921
<i>but suddenly my body felt
like it was heavier than lead.</i>

00:13:47.955 --> 00:13:50.594
<i>It took me
what felt like ages</i>

00:13:50.627 --> 00:13:53.265
<i>just to reach the house
right in front of me.</i>

00:13:59.879 --> 00:14:01.717
- I beg of you--

00:14:01.750 --> 00:14:04.221
Please, I beg of you--

00:14:04.254 --> 00:14:05.456
Oh, please, I...

00:14:05.490 --> 00:14:06.994
- Brother.

00:14:07.027 --> 00:14:09.598
You're alive? Brother!

00:14:13.807 --> 00:14:15.009
[groans]

00:14:21.455 --> 00:14:22.658
[grunts]

00:14:24.696 --> 00:14:26.866
- Please, dear God, Buddha,

00:14:26.900 --> 00:14:29.905
anyone out there
who's listening,

00:14:29.939 --> 00:14:31.976
I beg of you...

00:14:32.845 --> 00:14:34.716
save him.

00:14:34.749 --> 00:14:36.720
Please save my brother.

00:14:36.753 --> 00:14:39.257
He doesn't deserve
any of this.

00:14:39.290 --> 00:14:40.527
- [gasps]

00:14:42.898 --> 00:14:44.769
[crying]

00:14:44.802 --> 00:14:48.743
- My brother isn't like me.

00:14:48.777 --> 00:14:50.179
He's kind.

00:14:50.212 --> 00:14:54.555
He's a kindhearted kid
through and through.

00:14:54.588 --> 00:14:58.663
He says he wants to help others,

00:14:58.697 --> 00:15:02.470
but I got in the way
of his dream.

00:15:04.274 --> 00:15:05.944
It's my fault.

00:15:05.978 --> 00:15:09.384
I'm to blame, so please...

00:15:10.186 --> 00:15:12.658
please don't punish him.

00:15:12.691 --> 00:15:14.629
It's my fault...

00:15:14.662 --> 00:15:16.331
and only mine.

00:15:19.071 --> 00:15:21.041
The truth is...

00:15:21.075 --> 00:15:22.711
I've always known...

00:15:23.713 --> 00:15:25.517
about his name....

00:15:26.418 --> 00:15:29.925
The "mu" in "Muichiro"
stands for...

00:15:29.959 --> 00:15:31.996
- [groans]

00:15:39.812 --> 00:15:43.385
<i>- ...it stands for "infinity."</i>

00:15:44.588 --> 00:15:46.792
<i>- Mist Breathing, Fourth Form...</i>

00:15:46.826 --> 00:15:49.031
[demons jabber]

00:15:49.064 --> 00:15:52.270
<i>[sentimental music]</i>

00:15:54.141 --> 00:15:55.610
<i>- Shifting Flow Slash!</i>

00:15:57.615 --> 00:15:59.417
- [coughs]

00:15:59.451 --> 00:16:00.220
- Kotetsu!

00:16:00.253 --> 00:16:02.257
- [coughs] Mr. Tokito.

00:16:02.290 --> 00:16:05.129
Don't--
Don't worry about me.

00:16:05.162 --> 00:16:08.604
Mr. Haganezuka, you have to...

00:16:08.637 --> 00:16:11.976
save him and the swords!

00:16:12.010 --> 00:16:13.412
- [grunts]

00:16:14.682 --> 00:16:16.017
Right.

00:16:17.821 --> 00:16:20.894
- [grumbles]

00:16:20.927 --> 00:16:22.999
<i>Damn swordsmith.</i>

00:16:23.032 --> 00:16:24.602
<i>Damn philistine!</i>

00:16:24.635 --> 00:16:26.238
<i>His focus is absurd.</i>

00:16:26.271 --> 00:16:28.375
<i>It's practically inhuman!</i>

00:16:28.409 --> 00:16:30.346
<i>Even after
all I've done to him,</i>

00:16:30.379 --> 00:16:33.921
<i>he still won't stop
honing that damn sword!</i>

00:16:33.954 --> 00:16:36.391
<i>Even when I decimated
one of his eyes,</i>

00:16:36.424 --> 00:16:40.333
<i>he maintained his focus
sharpening that sword!</i>

00:16:40.366 --> 00:16:42.705
- [groaning]

00:16:42.738 --> 00:16:44.474
<i>- Ooh, I know!</i>

00:16:44.509 --> 00:16:47.882
<i>What if I tell him
I'm going to kill this one?</i>

00:16:47.915 --> 00:16:49.183
[gasps]

00:16:51.957 --> 00:16:54.161
<i>He managed to escape
the Water Prison Pot!</i>

00:16:54.194 --> 00:16:56.566
<i>But how is that possible?</i>

00:16:56.599 --> 00:16:57.635
<i>It shouldn't be.</i>

00:16:57.668 --> 00:16:59.939
<i>I was so certain
that his death was imminent,</i>

00:16:59.973 --> 00:17:02.744
<i>that he was the furthest thing
from my mind.</i>

00:17:03.747 --> 00:17:05.449
<i>No, wait a second.</i>

00:17:05.483 --> 00:17:07.721
<i>On the other hand,
I didn't notice he escaped,</i>

00:17:07.754 --> 00:17:11.262
<i>because I was so focused
on dealing with these two.</i>

00:17:11.295 --> 00:17:12.297
<i>Yes!</i>

00:17:12.330 --> 00:17:13.199
<i>Hmm?</i>

00:17:13.232 --> 00:17:14.502
<i>Hold on, hold on, hold on.</i>

00:17:14.535 --> 00:17:16.740
<i>What's with
that mark on his face?</i>

00:17:16.773 --> 00:17:20.346
<i>If I recall the information
Lord Muzan gave me,</i>

00:17:20.379 --> 00:17:21.683
<i>the child with the earrings</i>

00:17:21.716 --> 00:17:24.989
<i>is the one who has the mark
on his face, isn't he?</i>

00:17:25.022 --> 00:17:27.160
<i>No, no, no. It matters not.</i>

00:17:27.193 --> 00:17:30.332
<i>How are you standing there
so nonchalantly?</i>

00:17:30.366 --> 00:17:32.169
<i>The attack
I landed on you earlier</i>

00:17:32.203 --> 00:17:35.276
<i>should have left your body
completely paralyzed!</i>

00:17:35.309 --> 00:17:38.216
<i>And how were you able
to summon even greater speed</i>

00:17:38.249 --> 00:17:40.620
<i>than our last encounter
and wound me?</i>

00:17:43.126 --> 00:17:45.129
<i>Octopus Vase Hell!</i>

00:17:45.162 --> 00:17:46.733
[metal clangs]

00:17:46.766 --> 00:17:48.235
- Lord Tokito! [grunts]

00:17:49.872 --> 00:17:51.810
[wood clatters]

00:17:51.843 --> 00:17:54.013
- Hyo, hyo!

00:17:54.047 --> 00:17:56.151
You didn't expect
this octopus flesh

00:17:56.185 --> 00:17:57.521
to be so springy!

00:17:57.555 --> 00:17:59.825
Let's see you
try and slash this!

00:18:08.375 --> 00:18:10.747
<i>He's still honing that sword?</i>

00:18:10.780 --> 00:18:11.916
<i>Is he a fool?</i>

00:18:11.950 --> 00:18:14.220
<i>Surely he's not
in his right mind.</i>

00:18:14.254 --> 00:18:16.057
<i>His madness is sublime!</i>

00:18:16.091 --> 00:18:19.832
<i>The swordsmith can wait until
I've killed off the Hashira.</i>

00:18:19.865 --> 00:18:23.472
I'm sure you know this,
but I wasn't trying earlier.

00:18:23.507 --> 00:18:25.476
But this time,
I'll give it all I've got

00:18:25.510 --> 00:18:27.914
so I can crush and absorb you!

00:18:27.948 --> 00:18:29.585
[sword slashes]

00:18:29.618 --> 00:18:30.620
[gasps]

00:18:34.528 --> 00:18:38.235
- Mr. Kanamori, you crafted
this sword for me.

00:18:40.741 --> 00:18:43.378
Mr. Kanamori, thank you.

00:18:45.316 --> 00:18:48.255
- N--No, it was nothing!

00:18:48.289 --> 00:18:50.159
All I did was follow
the instructions

00:18:50.192 --> 00:18:52.196
your first swordsmith left me!

00:18:52.230 --> 00:18:54.668
- That's right.

00:18:54.702 --> 00:18:56.004
It was Mr. Tetsuido

00:18:56.037 --> 00:18:58.710
who forged my first sword
for me, wasn't it?

00:18:58.743 --> 00:19:01.481
But he's since passed away
from heart disease.

00:19:01.516 --> 00:19:02.618
<i>- Hmph!</i>

00:19:02.651 --> 00:19:05.155
<i>No matter how many times
you replace your sword,</i>

00:19:05.189 --> 00:19:06.993
<i>it won't change a thing.</i>

00:19:07.026 --> 00:19:09.230
<i>[sentimental music]</i>

00:19:12.838 --> 00:19:15.476
<i>- Ah. It fits like a glove.</i>

00:19:18.148 --> 00:19:21.020
- I worry about you
very much, boy.

00:19:21.054 --> 00:19:24.929
After all,
who could ever understand

00:19:24.962 --> 00:19:26.464
what it is you're going through?

00:19:27.500 --> 00:19:30.607
How you only have time
for battle and training?

00:19:30.641 --> 00:19:34.982
How you're barely getting by
and have no breathing room?

00:19:35.016 --> 00:19:36.786
How anxious
you must be all the time

00:19:36.820 --> 00:19:39.525
because you can't seem
to remember anything?

00:19:39.558 --> 00:19:42.631
And how you strive so hard,
you end up vomiting blood?

00:19:42.665 --> 00:19:46.706
Who could ever understand
something like that?

00:19:46.739 --> 00:19:50.313
Whenever I lay eyes on the
battered swords you've used,

00:19:50.346 --> 00:19:52.717
it brings a tear to my eye.

00:19:53.553 --> 00:19:56.291
Muichiro,
listen to me carefully.

00:19:56.325 --> 00:19:59.330
I feel I won't be around
much longer.

00:20:00.466 --> 00:20:03.105
But I'll still worry about you,

00:20:03.138 --> 00:20:04.942
even in the afterlife.

00:20:06.913 --> 00:20:09.952
<i>- Mr. Tetsuido, I'm sorry.</i>

00:20:09.985 --> 00:20:13.726
<i>I know I made you worry,
but I'm all right now.</i>

00:20:14.728 --> 00:20:17.033
<i>So rest easy.</i>

00:20:17.066 --> 00:20:18.402
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:20:18.435 --> 00:20:21.341
<i>Mist Breathing, Fifth Form...</i>

00:20:22.444 --> 00:20:24.615
<i>Sea of Clouds and Haze!</i>

00:20:29.357 --> 00:20:31.729
- Your rapid-fire chopping
had me worried,

00:20:31.762 --> 00:20:33.966
but it seems like you're
not able to keep up

00:20:34.000 --> 00:20:36.672
with my vase's speed after all!

00:20:36.706 --> 00:20:37.741
- Are you sure?

00:20:37.774 --> 00:20:38.943
- What?

00:20:38.976 --> 00:20:42.518
- Maybe it's because you've
lived for hundreds of years,

00:20:42.551 --> 00:20:44.955
but your senses
have grown weary.

00:20:46.024 --> 00:20:46.993
- [winces]

00:20:47.027 --> 00:20:49.264
- I'm going to behead you.

00:20:49.297 --> 00:20:51.502
I've got
much more important things to do

00:20:51.535 --> 00:20:53.573
then playing
with that silly vase of yours.

00:20:53.607 --> 00:20:57.981
- Heh! Don't underestimate me,
you damn brat.

00:20:59.685 --> 00:21:00.687
[grunts]

00:21:00.720 --> 00:21:06.097
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:21:06.130 --> 00:21:07.534
<i>- Muichiro...</i>

00:21:08.837 --> 00:21:11.942
<i>sorry I couldn't be
more gentle with you.</i>

00:21:13.044 --> 00:21:14.649
<i>It's just...</i>

00:21:14.682 --> 00:21:16.952
<i>I could never
afford to be that way.</i>

00:21:18.155 --> 00:21:19.992
<i>Being compassionate
towards others...</i>

00:21:20.026 --> 00:21:23.799
<i>is one more thing
that only the chosen can do.</i>

00:21:25.269 --> 00:21:27.607
<i>But remember, Muichiro...</i>

00:21:28.710 --> 00:21:31.616
<i>no matter how virtuous
a life you may lead,</i>

00:21:31.649 --> 00:21:32.952
<i>neither the gods nor Buddha</i>

00:21:32.985 --> 00:21:35.022
<i>will be the ones
to protect you in the end.</i>

00:21:36.458 --> 00:21:39.397
<i>That's why I threw myself
in front of you that day.</i>

00:21:40.466 --> 00:21:44.307
<i>Muichiro, you and I
are nothing alike...</i>

00:21:47.313 --> 00:21:49.718
<i>because for the sake
of someone else...</i>

00:21:51.622 --> 00:21:53.793
<i>you can exert infinite strength.</i>

00:21:53.826 --> 00:21:58.469
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:21:58.503 --> 00:22:01.709
<i>You are one of the chosen ones.</i>

00:22:02.911 --> 00:22:04.882
<i>["Koi Kogare" playing]</i>

00:22:04.915 --> 00:22:11.929
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:23:32.957 --> 00:23:34.529
[page rustles]

00:23:34.562 --> 00:23:37.366
- Oh, yeah! Happy Birthday,
Ms. Kanroji!

00:23:37.400 --> 00:23:38.637
- [grunts]

00:23:38.670 --> 00:23:40.908
- Let's start with your friends
from the Village!

00:23:40.941 --> 00:23:43.112
[Kotetsu] Our gift's
an all-you-can-eat spread!

00:23:43.145 --> 00:23:44.147
- [squeals]

00:23:44.180 --> 00:23:45.449
All-you-can-eat
means I can have

00:23:45.482 --> 00:23:47.086
as many helpings
as I want, right?

00:23:47.120 --> 00:23:49.792
- Huh? You're gonna
have seconds of all this?

00:23:49.825 --> 00:23:51.495
- Oh, my gosh! Oh, my gosh!
- Of course!

00:23:51.529 --> 00:23:52.597
- Oh, my gosh! Oh, my gosh!

00:23:52.631 --> 00:23:55.603
- Now it's time
for a Taisho-era secret!

00:23:55.637 --> 00:23:58.275
Nowadays, Ms. Kanroji's
favorite foods

00:23:58.309 --> 00:24:00.379
are pork cutlets
and omelet rice,

00:24:00.413 --> 00:24:02.951
which are both
Western-style foods.

00:24:02.985 --> 00:24:03.887
So as a surprise...

00:24:03.920 --> 00:24:07.493
Nezuko and I got her some
for her birthday!

00:24:07.528 --> 00:24:09.898
- Ahh! Thank you!

00:24:09.932 --> 00:24:11.167
Can I eat them now?

00:24:11.201 --> 00:24:13.004
- Of course!
- [grunts]

00:24:13.037 --> 00:24:17.380
- Up next, Episode 9,
"Mist Hashira Muichiro Tokito."

00:24:17.413 --> 00:24:18.381
- Seconds, please!

00:24:18.415 --> 00:24:19.585
- Already?

00:24:19.618 --> 00:24:21.689
- Come on! Keep 'em coming!

